sailpoint.api.nativeidentitychange

Class NativeIdentityChangeGenericPropagator

  • java.lang.Object
    • sailpoint.api.nativeidentitychange.AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator
      • sailpoint.api.nativeidentitychange.NativeIdentityChangeGenericPropagator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    NativeIdentityChangePropagator

    public class NativeIdentityChangeGenericPropagator
extends AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator
    This class provides an implementation of NativeIdentityChangePropagator that delegates all propagation logic to a rule. It has two configuration attributes:

    • ruleName : the name of a rule with type NativeIdentityChange which implements the propagation logic
    • targetClass : the full name (e.g., "sailpoint.object.Widget" of the class of object being handled

    The framework provided here will call AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator.haveAllObjectsProcessed(Class) and AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator.markAllObjectsProcessed(Class) as required. The rule may call AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator.hasObjectProcessed(Class, String) to avoid repeating propagation to already-processed objects on retry; it MUST call AbstractNativeIdentityChangePropagator.markObjectProcessed(Class, String) each time an object has been processed, saved and committed.

    Ideally, the target class should not match the class of any other configured propagators; if it does, care must be taken when using the objects-processed methods so that one propagator does not mark objects that the other propagator has not yet processed. Having different propagators which process disjoint sets of objects is strongly preferred.

    Rule implementations are responsible for handling all necessary locks/commits/rollbacks.
